	abstract = {The window function for protohalos in Lagrangian space is often assumed to be a top hat in real space. We measure this profile directly and find that it is more extended than a top hat but less extended than a Gaussian; its shape is well described by rounding the edges of the top hat by convolution with a Gaussian that has a scale length about 5 times smaller. This effective window Weff is particularly simple in Fourier space, and has an analytic form in real space. Together with the excursion set bias parameters, Weff describes the
