progenitor mass ratio ({\textasciitilde} ξ-2). We also present a simple
and accurate fitting formula for the mean mass growth rate of haloes as
a function of mass and redshift. This mean rate is 46Msolar
yr-1 for 1012Msolar haloes at z = 0,
and it increases with mass as {\textasciitilde} M1.1 and with redshift as (1
