	abstract = {We use a complete sample of about 140000 galaxies from the Sloan Digital
Sky Survey {(SDSS)} to study the size distribution of galaxies and its
dependence on their luminosity, stellar mass and morphological type. The
large {SDSS} data base provides statistics of unprecedented accuracy. For
each type of galaxy, the size distribution at given luminosity (or
stellar mass) is well described by a log-normal function, characterized
by its median and dispersion {σlnR.} For late-type
galaxies, there is a characteristic luminosity at Mr,0{\textasciitilde}-20.5
