Hα surveys reach a matched 3σ flux limit of ≈3
M⊙ yr-1 out to z = 2.2 for the first time,
while the wide area and the coverage over two independent fields allow
us to greatly overcome cosmic variance and assemble by far the largest
samples of Hα emitters. Catalogues are presented for a total of
1742, 637, 515 and 807 Hα emitters, robustly selected at z = 0.40,
0.84, 1.47 and 2.23, respectively, and used to determine the Hα
luminosity function and its evolution. The faint-end slope of the
Hα luminosity function is found to be α = -1.60 ±
